any as 20000 deaths from lung cancer each year and mike cook head 
of the epas office of drinking water said a few hundred of those 
may be caused by watersource radon 
radon a radioactive gas that can be concentrated in houses 
generally arises from the soil beneath a home working its way 
through foundation cracks or other entrances 
cook in an interview on a discussion on the usa today 
television show quoted results of a survey of wells across the 
country that said 72 percent had dangerously high radon levels 
</TEXT>
