terry povah is up to his 
warehouse ceiling in sweatshirts coffee mugs fishing tackle and 
thousands of other items normally carted home by tourists during a 
typical yellowstone summer 
but the summer of 88 was far from typical in the countrys 
first national park 
forest fires that raged over half of yellowstone national parks 
22 million acres meant evacuation and early closure of many 
facilities it also meant the hasty exit of thousands of visitors 
who ordinarily would crowd the aisles of povahs 15 retail stores 
past labor day 
will i have to reorder inventory for next year god i hope 
