montana by train in 1905 from st paul minn and went to work for 
the yellowstone park association which then ran the commissary 
through three generations of its owners grit hunches neck 
protrusion and luck hamilton stores which formally began in 1915 
when its founder bought out a retiring storekeeper at old faithful 
has grown into a multimilliondollar operation 
today hamilton stores concessions are scattered throughout the 
park they include service stations snack bars grocery and 
general merchandise stores and camera shops they also provide 12 
dormitories for their 800 summer employees 
povah says his family will remember this year for a long time 
it was wild he said shaking his head in may and june we 
