highly personal and court realism mike leigh high hopes 
about class tensions in the thatcher administration derek jarman 
the last of england about western civilization on the brink of 
the apocalypse and terence davies distant voices still 
lives about a familys troubled life 
sergei paradjanov who with andrei tarkovsky is considered 
among the most important soviet directors in decades will have the 
