thursday that the south africans given refuge agreed not to have 
contact with news media as a condition of their staying this was 
so the consulate could continue normal operations and avoid 
activities incompatible with diplomatic activity he said 
black activist winnie mandela visited the consulate wednesday 
and complained that us officials would not let the detainees 
contact reporters 
police pledged not to arrest the three initial escapees if they 
leave the consulate but law and order minister adriaan vlok 
confirmed that a multipronged crackdown against other activists is 
under way 
across south africa more than two dozen activists were detained 
or barred from political activities this week offices of 
antiapartheid groups were raided and pedestrians and motorists in 
urban centers were subjected to random searches 
