<TEXT>
heres a chronological look at some of the key events in the 
bank of new york cos hostile takeover attempt of irving bank 
corp 
sept 25 1987 bank of new york makes an unsolicited 14 
billion cashstock bid for irving 
oct 9 irvings board rejects the 14 billion bid activates 
the companys poison pill antitakeover defense 
nov 20 bank of new york lowers its offer to 12 billion 
citing the oct 19 stock market crash 
dec 15 irvings board rejects bank of new yorks 12 billion 
bid 
jan 25 1988 bank of new york lowers its bid to 108 
billion citing irvings decision to increase its fourthquarter 
loanloss reserve 
feb 16 irvings board rejects bank of new yorks 108 
billion bid 
feb 25 bank of new yorks takeover proposal gets approval 
from the federal reserve and new york state banking boards 
march 15 28 irving amends its poison pill 
april 14 bank of new yorks shareholders give their blessing 
to an irving merger 
april 18 banca commerciale italiana enters the picture 
offering 65 a share for 51 percent of irving irving announces a 
major resturcturing 
april 20 banca commerciale offers 75 a share for 45 percent 
of irving 
may 2 banca commerciale raises its proposed stake to 51 
percent at the same price 
may 6 irvings shareholders reelect irvings directors 
although bank of new york later challenges the proxy results in 
court 
may 23 banca commerciale raises its bid for 51 percent of 
irving to 80 a share the value of the offer is upped to 84 a 
share a few weeks later 
june 15 bank of new york conditionally offers to raise the 
stock portion of its bid valuing the offer at 14 billion irving 
later rejects the proposal the previous offer valued at about 
12 billion under current market conditions stands 
july 6 new york state supreme court strikes down a provision 
of irvings poison pill irving vows to appeal 
aug 19 the fed rules the italian government agency that owns 
most of banca commerciale has to supply financial information in 
the irving bid 
aug 29 banca commerciale withdraws its bid 
sept 7 fed grants bank of new york another 90day extension 
to complete the irving merger pending appeal of the poison pill 
case 
