that the owners of the seabrook nh nuclear power plant must 
prove they could one day pay to shut down the plant if they are to 
be allowed to operate 
the commission voted unanimously to require the owners the 
submit a plan within 30 days that shows a reasonable assurance 
that adequate funding would be available for decommissioning the 
plant 
